11 Section 1. Section 37-3-102, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "37-3-102. Definitions. Unless the context requires otherwise, in this chapter, the following definitions
13 apply:
14 (1) "ACGME" means the accreditation council for graduate medical education.
15 (2) "AOA" means the American osteopathic association.
16 (3) "Approved internship" means an internship training program of at least 1 year in a program that
17 either is approved for intern training by the AOA or conforms to the standards for intern training established by
18 the ACGME or successors. However, the board may, upon investigation, approve any other internship.
19 (4) (3) "Approved medical school" means a school that either is accredited by the AOA or conforms to
20 the education standards established by the LCME or the world health organization or successors for medical
21 schools that meet standards established by the board by rule.
22 (5) (4) "Approved residency" means a residency training program conforming to the standards for
23 residency training established by the ACGME or successors or approved for residency training by the AOA.
24 (6) (5) "Board" means the Montana state board of medical examiners provided for in 2-15-1731.
25 (7) (6) "Community-integrated health care" means the provision of out-of-hospital medical services
26 that an emergency care provider with an endorsement may provide as determined by board rule.
27 (8) (7) "Department" means the department of labor and industry provided for in Title 2, chapter 15,
28 part 17.
