8 Section 4. Section 37-26-301, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "37-26-301. Practice of naturopathic health care -- alternative health care formulary committee.
10 (1) Naturopathic physicians may practice naturopathic medicine as a limited practice of the healing arts as
11 exempted in 37-3-103(1)(m) (l), with the following restrictions. A naturopathic physician may not:
12 (a) prescribe, dispense, or administer any legend drug, as defined in 50-31-301, except for whole
13 gland thyroid; homeopathic preparations; the therapeutic substances, drugs, and therapies described in
14 subsection (2); and oxytocin (pitocin), provided that the naturopathic physician may administer but may not
15 prescribe or dispense oxytocin (pitocin);
16 (b) administer ionizing radioactive substances for therapeutic purposes;
17 (c) perform surgical procedures except those minor surgery procedures authorized by this chapter;
18 or
19 (d) claim to practice any licensed health care profession or system of treatment other than
20 naturopathic medicine unless holding a separate license in that profession.
21 (2) Naturopathic physicians may prescribe, administer, and dispense for preventive and
22 therapeutic purposes the following therapeutic substances, drugs, and therapies, as well as drugs as specified
23 by the formulary list provided for in subsection (3):
24 (a) food, food extracts, vitamins, minerals, enzymes, whole gland thyroid, botanical medicines,
25 homeopathic preparations, and oxytocin (pitocin);
26 (b) topical drugs, health care counseling, nutritional counseling and dietary therapy, naturopathic
27 physical applications, therapeutic devices, and nonprescription drugs; and
28 (c) barrier devices for contraception, naturopathic childbirth attendance, and minor surgery.
